# Resonant Shared Libraries

These libraries are used by both device and modem firmware via `lib_extra_dirs = ../shared_libs`.

## RESONANT_LR_RADIO
- SX1262 LoRa radio abstraction with dual-core safety
- Core 0 executes all radio operations; Core 1 sets request flags
- Handles single-packet and multi-packet TX/RX with automatic fragmentation
- Callbacks: onRxComplete, onTxComplete, onError
- Board-specific pin configs via `#ifdef BOARD_RAK3112` / default Heltec V3
- Config presets: getLoRaLongRangePreset(), getLoRaTelemetryPreset(), getFskBulkPreset()

## RESONANT_FRAME
- Wire Protocol v1 frame builder and validator
- 20-byte overhead: header(1) + length(2) + srcId(4) + dstId(4) + type(1) + options(1) + seqNum(4) + totalPkts(1) + pktIdx(1) + data(N) + checksum(1)
- Frame types: 0x01-0x0B (telemetry, metrics, commands, adoption, etc.)
- Source ID derived from ESP32 MAC address (last 4 bytes)

## RESONANT_ENCRYPTION
- ATECC608B abstraction with mbedTLS mock mode (ATECC_MOCK=1)
- ECDH (P-256), ECDSA sign/verify, AES-128-GCM encrypt/decrypt
- HKDF key derivation: salt="ResonantLR", info=version+sensorId+gatewayId
- X.509 certificate handling: load CA, verify chain, extract pubkey
- Device credential provisioning: loadDeviceCredentials()

## RESONANT_STORAGE
- NVS (Preferences) wrapper for persistent state
- Adoption state: parentId, ackFailCount, waitAfterTx
- Energy tracking, boot count, metrics timing
- StorageKeys namespace for all key constants

## RESONANT_POWER_MANAGER
- Deep sleep management with configurable duration
- Energy metering: pre-TX, TX, RX current draw profiles
- Wake timeout enforcement
- RTC memory energy buffer (survives deep sleep)

## Cross-cutting rules
- Changes to shared_libs affect both device and modem — test both after changes
- Radio library changes require testing on both RAK3112 and Heltec V3 pin configs
- Frame format changes must be synchronized with Python test scripts
